<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1475,2005]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis box="[199,316,1585,1609]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1585,1609]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Externally, the new species (
<figureCitation box="[637,701,1585,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) differs clearly from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Freyer" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[940,1037,1585,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Epimecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ustula">
<emphasis box="[940,1037,1585,1609]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">E. ustula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1054,1151,1585,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
) by its remarkably different forewing pattern resembling that of members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1906" box="[826,958,1621,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,958,1621,1645]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[973,1072,1621,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Figs 4–8</figureCitation>
). It is most similar to the Chinese (Qinghai, Kuku Nor (
<typeStatus box="[381,428,1657,1681]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">type</typeStatus>
locality) and Gansu, Xiahe) 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[736,820,1657,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatua">
<emphasis box="[736,820,1657,1681]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">L. fatua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[834,900,1657,1681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), but differs by its smaller size, ash-grey forewing ground colour (that is brownish in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[532,617,1693,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatua">
<emphasis box="[532,617,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">L. fatua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the configuration and colouration of the reniform and orbicular spots. Compared to the three other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1906" box="[456,588,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,588,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[814,938,1729,1753]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authority="(Staudinger, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[954,1432,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centralasiae">
<emphasis box="[954,1225,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges centralasiae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Staudinger, O. &amp; Rebel, H." box="[1238,1423,1729,1753]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" refId="ref1642" refString="Staudinger, O. &amp; Rebel, H. (1901) Catalog der Lepidopteren des palaearctischen Faunengebietes. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, 412 pp. [in German] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 120482" type="book" year="1901">Staudinger, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Ronkay, 2005" authorityName="L. Ronkay" authorityYear="2005" box="[151,553,1765,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varians">
<emphasis box="[151,370,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges varians</emphasis>
L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L." box="[405,553,1765,1789]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 57" refId="ref1776" refString="Ronkay, L. (2005) Revision of the genus Lophoterges Hampson, 1906 (s. l.) (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Cuculliinae). Part II. The genus Lophoterges s. str. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 51 (1), 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="2005">Ronkay, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Ronkay, 2005" authorityName="L. Ronkay" authorityYear="2005" box="[604,1009,1765,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radians">
<emphasis box="[604,824,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges radians</emphasis>
L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L." box="[860,1009,1765,1789]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 57" refId="ref1776" refString="Ronkay, L. (2005) Revision of the genus Lophoterges Hampson, 1906 (s. l.) (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Cuculliinae). Part II. The genus Lophoterges s. str. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 51 (1), 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="2005">Ronkay, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1127,1765,1789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Figs 6–8</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Benedek &amp; Babics &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis, 2020" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Babics &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2020" box="[1146,1228,1765,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Epimecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tekes" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1146,1228,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">E. tekes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1235,1294,1765,1789]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1235,1294,1765,1789]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the more monotonous ash-grey forewing ground colour with less prominent patterns and the more elongated, narrower and oblong forewing shape. The female genitalia of the new species (
<figureCitation box="[760,824,1837,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,188,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[164,1424,182,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Epimecia (9, 10) and Lophoterges (11–15) spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of specimens: 9, 12–15—BBT; 10— HNHM (photo by V.S. Kononenko); 11—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406516/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Freyer" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1210,1304,1837,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Epimecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ustula">
<emphasis box="[1210,1304,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">E. ustula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1318,1395,1837,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,188,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[164,1424,182,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Epimecia (9, 10) and Lophoterges (11–15) spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of specimens: 9, 12–15—BBT; 10— HNHM (photo by V.S. Kononenko); 11—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406516/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) by the more elongated apophyses anteriores and posteriores and conspicuously more elongated sclerotized anterior section of ductus bursae with the anterior bar more strongly extending to the cervix bursae. The female genitalia of the new species are remarkably different from those of the four mentioned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1906" box="[768,900,1945,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[768,900,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
